06.","meanings":["English: habitational name from a place in the parish of Alstonfield, Staffordshire named Beresford, from Old English <i>beofor</i> ‘beaver’ (or possibly from a byname from this word) + Old English <i>ford</i> ‘ford’. This name also became established in Ireland.","History: The first recorded bearer of the surname is John <i>de Beveresford</i>, who held the manor of Beresford, Staffordshire, from <i>c.</i> 1220 to 1241. All present-day Beresfords are apparently descended from Thomas Beresford, who fought at Agincourt in 1415 and who fathered sixteen sons and five daughters. The Irish branch of the family includes the Marquesses of Waterford."],"variants":[{"name":"Berisford","meanings":["English: variant of   Beresford  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"John de Beresforde was born in 1310, in Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 2 sons with Emma Bagnolde. He died in 1349, at the age of 39."},"et":{"1310–1349":"1310–1349","1285–1320":"1285–1320","1320–1360":"1320–1360","1350–1411":"1350–1411","1349":"1349","1411":"1411","1310":"1310","1320":"1320","1285":"1285","1350":"1350","1360":"1360","Beresford,  Derbyshire England":"Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Beresford Stafford England":"Staffordshire, England"},"fi":{"1310–1349":"1310–1349","1285–1320":"1285–1320","1320–1360":"1320–1360","1350–1411":"1350–1411","1349":"1349","1411":"1411","1310":"1310","1320":"1320","1285":"1285","1350":"1350","1360":"1360","Beresford,  Derbyshire England":"Derbyshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Beresford Stafford England":"Staffordshire, England"},"fr":{"1310–1349":"1310–1349","1285–1320":"1285–1320","1320–1360":"1320–1360","1350–1411":"1350–1411","1349":"1349","1411":"1411","1310":"1310","1320":"1320","1285":"1285","1350":"1350","1360":"1360","Beresford,  Derbyshire England":"Derbyshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","